  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a pragmatic, adaptive, open-label, randomized, multicenter phase II/III study
      consisting of two parts: Phase II and Phase III. In both study parts, patients will be
      randomized to two treatment arms (Arm A: best supportive care [BSC] + IFX-1; Arm B: BSC
      alone). After all patients are treated in Phase II, an interim analysis will be performed to
      assess the clinical benefit of the treatment using the assessed clinical parameters.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
